The paper deals with multi-agent learning and reinforcement learning, which are typically studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The specific game setting analyzed in the paper is a linear quadratic game, which falls under the game theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The analysis also involves the use of coupled Ricatti equations, which are commonly used in control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of policy-gradient algorithms in multi-agent settings, which is a topic of interest in the multi-agent systems (cs.MA) sub-category.
